headline: Snap-on (NYSE:SNA) Misses Q4 CY2025 Revenue Estimates
summary: Professional tools and equipment manufacturer Snap-on (NYSE:SNA) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales falling 5.2% year on year to $1.23 billion. Its GAAP profit of $4.94 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
